CME Group Plans to Launch Sovereign Yield Futures Next Month

-- B y   G a r t h   T h e u n i s s e n
-- 
2011-04-21T11:57:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/cme-group-plans-to-launch-sovereign-yield-futures-next-month.html
CME Group Inc. (CME) , the Chicago-based
derivatives exchange operator, plans to introduce Sovereign
Yield Spread futures on May 22 with trading scheduled to begin
the following day, the company said in a statement today.  Investors will initially be able to trade futures contracts
in the bond yields of France,  Germany , Italy, Netherlands, the
U.K. and the U.S., according to the statement. The contracts
will be settled in cash and will be known as ‘sovys,’ CME said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Garth Theunissen in London 
 gtheunissen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
